  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `communicationApi.ts` (post-task-005) to confirm `SendCommunicationError` export + `sendCommunication()` signature + how `authenticatedFetch` is currently parameterized.</step>
    <step order="2">Read `.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md` + `fluent-v9-component/SKILL.md` for Fluent v9 + `makeStyles` + `tokens` patterns.</step>
    <step order="3">Read existing wizard with `forwardRef` + `useImperativeHandle` in `CreateRecordWizard/` for shape mirroring.</step>
    <step order="4">Author `EmailComposer.types.ts`:
      - `EmailComposerMode = 'compose' | 'view' | 'reply' | 'forward' | 'draft'`
      - `EmailComposerMount = 'inline' | 'dialog' | 'page'`
      - `EmailComposerBodyFormat = 'html' | 'plaintext'`
      - `IComposerAssociation { entityName: string; recordId: string; primaryName?: string }`
      - `IComposerAttachmentSource { kind: 'local' | 'spe' | 'related' | 'wizard'; config?: unknown }`
      - `IValidationResult { field: 'to' | 'cc' | 'bcc' | 'subject' | 'body' | 'attachments' | 'from'; code: string; message: string }`
      - `EmailComposerState { mode; mount; from; to; cc; bcc; subject; body; bodyFormat; attachments; associations; isDirty; isSending; validationErrors }`
      - `EmailComposerAction` discriminated union: `SET_FIELD`, `SET_MODE`, `ADD_ATTACHMENT`, `REMOVE_ATTACHMENT`, `SET_VALIDATION_ERRORS`, `BEGIN_SEND`, `END_SEND`, `RESET`
      - `IEmailComposerProps { mode; mount; communicationId?; initialTo?; initialCc?; initialBcc?; initialSubject?; initialBody?; initialBodyFormat?; associations?; attachmentSources?; wizardContext?; authenticatedFetch; onSent?; onError?; onStateChange? }`
      - `IEmailComposerHandle { validate: () => IValidationResult[]; send: () => Promise&lt;void&gt;; saveDraft: () => Promise&lt;void&gt;; getState: () => EmailComposerState }`
    </step>
    <step order="5">Author `EmailComposer.reducer.ts`:
      - `initialState(props: IEmailComposerProps): EmailComposerState` — derives from props (mode, mount, initial* fields)
      - `emailComposerReducer(state, action): EmailComposerState` — pure switch over action types; immutable updates</step>
    <step order="6">Author `EmailComposer.tsx`:
      - `forwardRef&lt;IEmailComposerHandle, IEmailComposerProps&gt;((props, ref) => { ... })`
      - `useReducer(emailComposerReducer, props, initialState)`
      - `useImperativeHandle(ref, () => ({ validate: () => state.validationErrors, send: stubSend, saveDraft: stubSaveDraft, getState: () => state }))`
      - Mount-variant layout via `makeStyles` + `tokens` — three style objects keyed on mount:
        * `pageStyles` — full width, generous padding, section divider tokens, bottom-right action bar slot
        * `dialogStyles` — `maxWidth: 600px`, compressed padding, dialog header/footer slots
        * `inlineStyles` — no chrome wrapping (let wizard frame supply it); only inner content slots
      - Render skeleton slots: `&lt;HeaderRegion /&gt;` (page+dialog only), `&lt;RecipientsRegion /&gt;`, `&lt;SubjectRegion /&gt;`, `&lt;BodyRegion /&gt;`, `&lt;AttachmentsRegion /&gt;`, `&lt;ActionsRegion /&gt;` (page+dialog only) — each is `&lt;div role="region" aria-label="..."&gt;TODO sub-component slot&lt;/div&gt;` (filled in by 012-019)
      - Stub `validate()` returns `[]` (task 020 implements the real validation contract)
      - Stub `send()` throws `new Error('send() not yet implemented; pending sub-components')` — wizards will wire after sub-components land
      - Stub `saveDraft()` ditto
    </step>
    <step order="7">Update `EmailComposer/index.ts`: add `export { EmailComposer } from './EmailComposer'; export type { IEmailComposerProps, IEmailComposerHandle, EmailComposerMode, EmailComposerMount, EmailComposerState, IValidationResult, IComposerAssociation, IComposerAttachmentSource } from './EmailComposer.types';`</step>
    <step order="8">Update shared lib `src/index.ts`: uncomment the `export * from './components/EmailComposer';` line added in task 010.</step>
    <step order="9">Run `npm run build` + `npm run lint` in `@spaarke/ui-components`. Both MUST be clean.</step>
