  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`EmailComposer.tsx` compiles; engine renders without runtime error for all 15 mode × mount combinations (smoke-test via a temporary story or inline test).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Engine `forwardRef`s and exposes `IEmailComposerHandle` with `validate`, `send`, `saveDraft`, `getState` methods.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">State is managed via a SINGLE `useReducer` — no `useState` calls for engine state (other than refs / transient UI state).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Engine does NOT `import` anything from `@spaarke/auth` (verified by grep — NFR-02).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Engine uses only `@fluentui/react-components` primitives + `makeStyles` + `tokens` (ADR-021).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Mount-variant styling visible: page = full-width form chrome; dialog = ~600px bounded; inline = no header/action chrome (NFR-03).</criterion>
