  <notes>
    Engine intentionally ships in "skeleton" form here. Validation contract (FR-08) fills in via task 020. Sub-components fill the slots via 012-019. Modes (view/reply/forward/draft pre-fill logic) via 024-027. Tests via 028.

    Imperative handle pattern is the key — wizard hosts will hold a `composerRef = useRef&lt;IEmailComposerHandle&gt;()` and call its methods on user actions. This pattern lets the wizard own the "Finish" button while the composer remains agnostic to wizard chrome.

    Per CLAUDE.md Empirical Finding #2: `SendCommunicationError` is added by Wave 0 task 005 — DO NOT define it again here; import from `communicationApi.ts`.

    Dark mode: ADR-021 mandates dark-mode-by-default via Fluent theme provider. Engine does NOT manage its own theme — host's `FluentProvider` propagates. Manual confirm: render in dev with dark theme and verify no hardcoded colors.
  </notes>

